Tinnitus:

• Tinnitus refers to a ringing or buzzing sound in the ears

Symptoms to look for:

• Buzzing noise in the ears
• It can cause:
   o Bad sleep
   o Lack of concentration 

Causes:

• Damage to the nerve endings of the inner ear
• This damage is caused by:
   o Ageing
   o Exposure to loud noise
   o Foreign matter or wax in the ear
   o Allergies
   o High or low blood pressure
   o Diabetes
   o Neck injury
   o Head injury
   o Certain medication, which includes sedatives, anti-depressants, aspirin, etc.

Natural home remedy using basil leaves:

1. Take a handful of basil leaves
2. Crush them to a paste
3. Press this paste on a sieve
4. Extract the juice
5. Heat till lukewarm
6. Put 2 drops in the affected area
7. Repeat 2 times everyday

Natural home remedy using onions:

1. Slice and crush 1 onion to make a paste
2. Press the paste on a sieve
3. Extract the juice
4. Pour 2 drops in the affected ear

